#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/markers.rst:21
msgid ""
"Markers in the picture below are the yellow flags inside the clip. Not to be "
"confused with :ref:`timeline markers <guides>` (red flags in the picture "
"below). Markers are inside the clips and move with the clips."
msgstr ""

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/markers.rst:25
msgid ""
"Markers can be used for certain points (Marker2) or ranges (Marker1) in a "
"clip that are important."
msgstr ""

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/markers.rst:27
msgid ""
"Markers are clip related and \"fix\" to this clip. When you put the same "
"clip again in the timeline and you change a marker, this marker is changed "
"on both clips simultaneously."
msgstr ""

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/markers.rst:33
msgid "2 ways to add markers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/markers.rst:35
msgid ""
"Add markers to your clips via the :ref:`ui-monitors_clip_monitor`. That "
"allows you to preview the clip at the location where you are adding a marker."
msgstr ""

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/markers.rst:37
msgid ""
"Following procedures add a marker at the playhead position (clip monitor, "
"timeline):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/markers.rst:40
msgid "**Menu**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/markers.rst:42
msgid ""
"Clip monitor: From the main menu choose :menuselection:`Markers --> Add "
"Marker`, :ref:`add_marker`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/markers.rst:43
msgid ""
"Timeline: Click on the clip. From the main menu choose :menuselection:"
"`Markers --> Add Marker`, :ref:`add_marker`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/markers.rst:44
msgid ""
"Clip monitor: Right click on the clip monitor and choose :menuselection:"
"`Markers --> Add Marker`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../cutting_and_assembling/markers.rst:45
msgid ""
"Timeline: Right click the clip in the timeline and choose :menuselection:"
"`Markers --> Add Marker`. The marker is added at the play-head position."
msgstr ""

